This paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, specifically slot filling and relation extraction, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed approach utilizes deep neural networks, which are a popular tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of attention mechanisms is also a common technique in both natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also mentions the incorporation of external knowledge bases, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of dependency structures as input is a specific technique within natural language processing, which further supports the likelihood of cs.CL as the most likely sub-category.
